The paper deals with linear regression, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses memory and sample tradeoffs, which are related to information theory and data structures, respectively, and thus could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The lower bounds presented in the paper are based on probabilistic arguments and involve analyzing the behavior of random variables, which are typical techniques used in probability theory and stochastic processes, and thus could fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of its results for continuous optimization, which is a topic that could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
